  "description": "From the Publisher Check out your enigma-solving skills and see if you have the ability to become a master codebreaker! Alan Turing is renowned as the father of modern computing and, most importantly, for his intelligence work at Bletchley Park in cracking the Enigma cipher machine during World War II. Supporting the work of The Turing Trust, the charity set up by Alan’s family in his memory to provide computers to schools in Africa, celebrating his legacy in computer development, this collection of challenging and innovative codebreaking puzzles has been specially created to test your all-round codebreaking skills. As you work through the book, you will find the puzzles become progressively harder, but if you are in need of a little help, there’s a special hints section, and the solutions lead you step-by-step through the logic of every puzzle.",
